Preamble

The GNU General Public Licenses are designed to make sure that you have freedom to share and change all your software.  By contrast, the GNU Affero General Public License is intended to ensure your freedom to share and change all software that is used over a network.

When you distribute this software, you must give the recipients all the rights that you have. You must make sure that they, too, receive or can get the source code. If you use this software on a server, you must make the source code available over the network, so that everyone else also has that opportunity.

This license was originally written for use in software distribution. The licenses are designed to be used for any kind of software distribution. They apply equally to both proprietary and free software.

